76561198024259443,Recommended,281610,20726501,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,Solais,"A quite awesome addition to the dying RTS genre, Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak done a prequel story perfectly: setting up story points that were kinda ""out there"" in the originals, turning the game into a well made ""new first game"" of the series (chronologically speaking). There are obvious problems, especially when it comes to the braindead AI in multiplayer, but if you're someone who's more into singleplayer RTS games, this one is just right for you.I do have to say that it seemed like I found the exact opposite what everyone else was talking about regarding the campaign, including TotalBiscuit. They said the campaign is very easy, there are too many resources, you get unit types out of the blue without explanation, etc. I found all this to be false, as I had a rough time on Normal difficulty, I was always out of resources, and every single unit type you get is explained. So that particular criticism is weird for me. But maybe it's just me.So yeah. I'd recommend this game to RTS fans, and especially those who were fans of the original Homeworld games. It's rare if we get RTS games nowadays, so this is definitely one shining diamond.(One more note: The game is called -Deserts- of Kharak. So don't be surprised if all the maps are set in a desert.)"
