,Recommended,281610,20794662,"Posted: 27 January, 2016",all,Ph.G.,"Simply put, I think this is the most brilliant RTS to be released since Starcraft: Brood War - coming from someone with thousands of career games in SCBW and SC2, someone who is as competitive and serious about multiplayer RTS gaming as they come.The statements I'm making in this review are based on approximately 50 hours of play in multiplayer with approximately 90 games under my belt and a 60% win ratio.The tactical combat in this game is deep and exhilirating.  Ignore the small unit roster - each unit occupies a very specific role and has nuance and depth in their usage.  Ignore the ""boring desert maps"" complaints of others - the desert is a hidden unit in your army.  Its dunes will shield your vulnerable units, and their peaks will give your killers their perfect shots.  If you cooperate with the desert and allow it to shape your play, you will be victorious.  If you disregard it, you will be punished by the opponent who doesn't.  Ignore the ""two factions are very similar"" complaint, because that couldn't be further from the truth - while each faction has analogous units that ostensibly occupy similar roles, they end up functioning and feeling very different in practice.  I would be highly surprised if anyone making that statement has as much time with the game playing both factions as I do.The BW similarities come in the form of the incredible lethality and power of the tools at your disposal.  Everything is overpowered, therefore nothing is overpowered.  One well-placed unit executing a properly positioned ability can decimate an entire army.Unlike Broodwar and unlike many other RTSes that come before, this game is far more about how you use your units than anything else.  You don't need 500 APM, you don't have to have 10 minute long build orders memorized.  If your opener is even slightly optimized, you will never face a situation where you are defenseless - you will never face a coin-flip loss.  You can defeat much larger forces than your own with a few well-controlled units.  You will spend 90% of your time in a multiplayer match watching your army and controlling it, and 10% or less managing your economy and research.  The flow of gameplay results in a smooth and pure tactical experience.If you are a serious competitive RTS gamer, do yourself a huge favor and buy this game.  Ignore the region lock nonsense - sure, it's hampering ranked matchmaking, but nothing is stopping you from joining public matches and enjoying this incredibly tactically nuanced experience.As more maps are added and other mp issues get ironed out, this game will become a true masterpiece as a competitive MP rts goes.  Don't be left out.  You won't regret buying HWDOK."
