76561198023859189,Recommended,281610,22770520,"Posted: 2 May, 2016",all,BabbleIncognito,"I liked it. And I'm biased because I am also loyal to the brand. I've played Homeworld 1&2 when they first came out (they are in my nostalgia wishlist of things to get). The controls felt natural. The command playstyle was very Homeworld 1&2. It's a place where I was comfortable.If you collect RTS this is one to add to your collection. It's a good, straightforward and solid RTS.However, If you're looking for something unique, this game isn't the place to get it.Things I noticed and gave nod to was the height map terrains giving defilade and enfilade(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enfilade_and_defilade)actual meaning. The homeworld version of the mothership was upgradeable and not defensless.My biggest complaint is there isn't a lot of depth of gameplay. I completed the single player (distracted) in less than 8 hours. There aren't many ways to skin the cat (strategies that win the game) the story left me wanting more. I didn't feel challenged in the multiplayer and skirmish options. I've noticed that a lot from games recently, where they release a stable first product then pile on DLC's to increase the revenue. I get the sense this game will have more depth once the DLC's start rolling out."
