,Recommended,281610,23814730,"Posted: 25 June, 2016",all,Mr.Snork,"One of the only Games I ever pre-ordered. A solid entry for the Homeworld series.  You'll see a whole bunch of niggles by people in the reviews and comments, but by and large these are fairly minor issues. I myself would feel it desperately needs a ""pause and give orders option"" which was present in all the other games, However I wouldn't give it a negative review simply for that, (although it is pretty bad in my eyes).The biggest drawback is that its really been set-up as a multiplayer game, kinda like a tournament type, which when you consider the pedigree of Gearbox, isn't all that surprising. And you cant really blame Gearbox as MP seems to be where young gamers are these days and thus so is the money.  For me the emphasis has been on a thoughtful, singleplayer game you can take your time with. A result of this is that most of the sides are somewhat bland and homogeneous, (equal), and there is little differentiation between the opposing sides units.  Assymetric warfare, this is not.Practical Upshot:  If Multiplayer is your thing, you'll prob really enjoy this.  If you want a deep thoughtful RTS, you may want to think twice about this, unless its on sale.  It's not bad, but depth and ability to take your time, (away from a frantic MP pace), is not its strong point.  The Original HW games were far better at that.It is fun though, and definitely has all the flavour and feel of the original HW games."
