76561197983029034,Recommended,281610,28253955,"Posted: 8 December, 2016",all,NUMBNUTTS,"Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak is an exceptional addition to the Homeworld franchise. It has many different features to the space RTS predicessor and many, many similarities which make it easy to slide into. I will lay these datails out in the pros and cons.Pros:1) The feel and control of the game is virtually the same, with very minor differences such as a stream lined sensor use.2) The visuals are fantastic and the sounds, voices and interactions are perfectly in tuned with the original productions.3) The story is strong and connects strongly and perfectly with the original stories.4) Love the way that aerial vehicles were used in this game. Feels more authentic as they are called in for a singular strike and must RTB for refuel and re-arm before another strike may be made.5) Topography matters. Placement of units on high ground or low ground matters. You can also use topographical elements such as large sand dunes to conceal your units from long range strikes from rail guns so that they must close the distance in order to engage your units so that you can overwhelm them in short order.Cons:1) The campaign is short, you can see my time is only 8 hours. Those 8 hours were spent on the campaign from beginning to end on normal difficulty.2) The Unit selection for production is not as vast and diverse as the original series. This however can be explained away with the fact that this game takes place before the advancements in technology in the original games.3) Once you getSiege Cruisersand screen them behindbattle or assault cruiserswith support cruisers the game plays itself, it is the Homewold version of the Star Craft Carrier Spam.Overall the game is fantastic, any fan of the original series or new comer will fill right at home and will love playing this game."
