,Recommended,281610,20829700,"Posted: 29 January, 2016",all,integ3r,"Singleplayer delivers the homeworld feel pretty well. The feeling of isolation and limited resources is really nice. The persistent units and veterancy helps with giving you a sense of what is at stake.However it is short, and the AI isn't anything special but is challenging enough in the campaign as it can spawn tons of units and is heavily scripted.Skirmish isn't great, as there's too few maps and the AI cannot counter air units and in general isn't very good.Multiplayer isn't great either. The tech tree isn't entirely visible, so you'll have to memorize it while the gameplay is mostly focused on ""getting a bigger blob"" of units than your opponent.The game is not very focused on decisionmaking or strategy. There's little sense of ""outsmarting"" your opponent as it is you're ""outplaying"" him by keeping up your production constantly, getting the upgrades at the right times and expanding at the right time. You're not setting traps or making elaborate plans. You're just building units and trying to keep your economy intact while doing it.Some units have special abilities but they are not the focal point of the gameplay.TL;DR: The singleplayer campaign is interesting. Skirmish and multiplayer is not very interesting."
