76561198077720094,Recommended,281610,24030415,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,Maverik,"Just finished the camaign and absolutely loved the entire playthrough. Engaging storyline, fresh units, classic combat style and nice graphics backed by excellent voice acting, I couldn't stop playing the game until I had it seen it through to the end!Definitely recommended for both new & old players of homeworld, The game makes an effort to stay true to its homeworld roots while bringing something fresh to the table as a sequel.My only gripe: it ended too fast! 9 hours in, I've finished campaign with little effort (at normal difficulty). While I'll revisit the missions at classic difficulty now, it's unlikely to take me more than 24 hours of gameplay to finish it at this rate. Still, it's not a big con as the campaign is meant to get you comfortable with the game and it does that quite well. Now for the real challenge, I have to explore the multiplayer side of things where homeworld has always shined.Tips for players new to the game or genre:The AI in this game appears to have unlimited resources. It doesn't harvest anything so if you're hoping to just wait it out, it'll never stop sending squads your way. Yet instead of taking it as a negative aspect, use it! It's an excellent way to level your units up and raise their ranks if you position them correctly with a supporting cruiser backing them.Make extensive use of Rachael's hacking & emp ability. The enemies railgun cruiser is devestating in large enough numbers and can only be acquired through hacking (hacking requires upgrade for this but you will get it in due course of campaign)Units are precious as experience is hard to come by. Take care of your units. You may have a lot of resource at hand but new units cannot replace your veterans right out of factory. Make sure you keep them safe."
