76561198082058174,Recommended,281610,29597467,Posted: 30 January,all,_Remigio_,"The good-Prequel to a classic. All pros of the space RTS carry over.-Solid RTS you expect from Homeworld.  There is a good reason to delay finishing a mission to harvest resources. Surviving untis carry over to the next mission and each has a purpose, abilities, and strenghs and weakness to consider.-Terrain elevation and line of sight really makes a difference. Terrain will show deformation and burnt chassis.-Each level bring a unique obstacle to overcome.-Some enemy units and tactics can feel cheap and spammy but preperation and good strategy will always win out. It helps to be patient and methodical and it feels tremendous when you overcome.-Tactical overlay is better than ever.-Strong narrative. A Focused origin story. Handles themes of systemic oppression and religious fervor quite well.  Its dramatic, somber, compelling, well paced and expressed with beautifully illustred animatics.-Visuals are pretty. The Desert is vibrant and varied. Explosions kick up big plums of sand. Wear and tear show up on selected vehicles and debris liters the sands.-The audio is nothing short of outstanding. The voice work is strong, the OST is recognizable and adds more of the Middle-eastern flair that's familiar to Homeworld and something that you would expect from being in a desert but the sound effects and Ambience is where this game really shines. Everything from vehicles driving on dunes, random radio chatter, gunfire, missile volleys, hits and ricochets, explosions, battle chatter, and aerial vehicles swooshing overhead is so atmospheric that it would be forgiven to overhear it and mistake it as real.  I'd go so far as to say that the tactical ambience is revolutionary for the RTS genre as a whole.The bad-The game can crash. Crashing after logging 30mins+ into a mission that's going well is irratating beyond emotes.-No keybindings! A PC game in 2016 (last i played) what a sacrilege.The ugly-My system more than meets the requirements but the game can get glitchy in long play sessons. Debris and burnt chassis can cause crashes if they keep getting strewn all over the battlefiled.-Clipping and units will sometimes phase through each other.-Units can freeze in place and spaz out from time to time.Despite the bugs if you're an RTS fan, Homeworld as a whole is definitely worth playing and worth the price of admission. Thank you Gearbox and Blackbird."
