,Recommended,281610,20775046,"Posted: 26 January, 2016",all,123,"This was a great pre-quel to a Real Time Strategy game that revolutionized an industry. The dynamics of playing on land rather then space but still keeping the feel of the original game are observed.  The story campaign is short, sweet, and full of drama and a real plot unlike most stories.  The gameplay is quick, many units counter other units,  geography is key as height gives you an advantage when shooting down on your oppenent. The graphics are beauitul the gameplay is great. Its one of the better Real Time Strategy games out there. Iv'e played over a dozen hours on Multiplayer they are always fun experiences. The only badside is lack of maps but the developers are going to release more soon.A lot of the issues brought up by people are being observed by the Developeres and they are going to be releasing patches with updates, new Maps, Replay ability and more. I believe they wanted to test the waters and make a great gameplay and later on when they had the resources give the game the much needed polishing it needs to be an outstanding Real Time Strategy game."
,Recommended,281610,20673670,"Posted: 21 January, 2016",all,MoD || Fr0z7y,"im recommending this game for a few reasons, namely because it's a ""prequel"" to the homeworld series which will open up more of the story and let you play through it, also because it does feel like homeworld.the game itself feels like homeworld. the units are different, but pretty much act and feel a lot like what you would see in the current landscape of war on our planet with some other high tech stuff mixed in, but not a lot. it's very realistic feeling, even for it being sci-fi. some of the things they have in this game are not far fetched in the scope of them being able to be used here on our planet, if we didn't have water that is. the planet is actually from what i can tell, a lot bigger than earth, which gives a lot of scope to the realism of having massive aircraft carriers that have wheels and rolling across huge seas of sand.the reason i say it feels like homeworld is the resource harvesting, the overlay, the ui, the maps, the radar screen, even some of the sounds when you have a unit selected. they start talking like they did in homeworld and it kind of freaked me out a little bit the first time i heard some of them talking about there being contacts nearby and what not. some of them would say some pretty cool stuff when there were no contacts nearby. the way you move units with attack move will show you the line of sight option as well as the elevation of the world. the unit cap increases as you go along and collect artifacts. you can capture units with your science officer, but be careful about going over unit cap as you can not capture planes to my knowledge (as in i havent tried it) and if you go over unit cap u will not be able to replace your planes. the planes (there are 3 types) are going to really make a difference in this game.for some tips:-use your aircraft carrier as a mobile gun/support craft with aa and move it closer to the fight as much as possible, if not even using it as a main target to draw fire at times repairing it with your support vehicles and letting your other units fight, this is especially helpful when you are out of cu's and they have a lot of aa and u cant get any more cu on the map.-support units are your friends but will not be able to autorepair themselves unless u find a module mid-late game, so use a couple support modules for your main group of fighting units-always keep cu available for your baserunners and the shipbreaking abilities from your salvagers/rachel-always keep as many planes as possible in your carrieri played this on classic difficulty, i restarted from a save at the beginning of one mission in the very early game because i kept screwing up. then only one mission did it make me restart mid-late game because i couldnt keep the objective, aced it and captured units after i did it the second time.10/10 for massive air game and ground game10/10 for prequel to homeworld10/10 for quality productbuy this game so we can play on multiplayer please..."
