76561198009689646,Recommended,281610,22987842,"Posted: 14 May, 2016",all,dave4985,"Deserts of Kharak is essentially Homeworld on a planet's surface.  That's the best description I can come up with.  Various vehicles act as near-direct counterparts to ships from the previous two space-side games.  You research to upgrade your units, build up your forces by sending out mining teams, and manage your forces to stay under the population cap, same as Homeworld. Terrain offers minor advantages or disadvantages compared to space, but overall the gameplay is more of the same.  The story plays out through movies with a painting-like aesthetic between missions or in-engine cutscenes during the missions.  Without spoilers, it's a decent story, if that sort of thing matters to you, not superior to original Homeworld but still very solid.In short, if you liked Homeworld, you'll probably dig DoK.  If you were looking for more than that, you'll probably be disappointed.  I myself liked it just fine."
