76561198027381519,Recommended,281610,29666750,Posted: 3 February,all,fallenbirdman,"I have been a fan of the Homeworld franchise since I picked up Homeworld 2 off the shelf.  These are great games, and Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak did not disappoint.  I will only cover three main points that really stood out to me.The first is RTS controls.  This game has very similar straight forward controls like the the previous games.  If you play RTSs this won't be difficult for you.  I recommend using mixed units when fighting the enemy.The second thing I want to mention is unit detail.  I love realism, and Homeworld never fails.  I will say that I expected more out of this game.  It does look beautiful, but I was more impressed with Homeworld 2's level of detail than this game.  Explosions really disappointed me.  Still beautiful, but not as impressed as usual.The last thing I will mention is the campaign story.  Multiplayer doesn't really excite me unless I'm playing with a friend or two.  If you are looking for that same style of storyline as the previous games, you will find it here.  I really feel like this is an actual history of this race of people when I'm playing.  The seamless transtion from cinematics to gameplay is just like the old games.  I love playing through the story...which is challenging as usual.I recommend this games to Homeworld fans.  If you haven't played the others, I recommend you play the more recent Homeworld Remastered release."
