,Recommended,281610,29596133,Posted: 30 January,all,GigaStoat,"A worthy successor to the original space operas (themselves having arguably the best RTS campaigns ever made).The scale is obviously smaller, with interceptors and jump drives replaced with dune buggies and trundling from point to point in a hulking carrier on tank tracks, though it retains Homeworld's epic sweep and punchy story beats.You won't be building impenetrable fortresses among the dunes or building huge fleets to overwhelm your enemies - there's no structures and you'll be scraping by each mission with a handful of units (at least on higher difficulties). This makes for a more focused and frantic RTS experience where you'll be concentrating on positioning and using each unit's special abilities to give you the advantage - for example, activating your Light Armored Vehicle's speed boost to charge through an opponent's front lines to take out their hard-hitting railguns, or laying down smokescreens to allow weaker units to escape.The campaign doesn't outstay its welcome and there's surprising variety to be found in the maps given that they're essentially all vast sandpits. It would be fair to say it's pretty light on content, and it feels somewhat of a proof of concept for a more substantial entry in the franchise, but it's clear that the devs understand what makes a Homeworld game tick and I'm excited to see where they go from here. The way light vehicles swarm around bigger targets is very reminiscent of the balletic dogfights in the original two games and the soundtrack and hand-drawn cutscenes are on-point for the series.Great to see HW back and on form!"
76561198128696082,Recommended,281610,29819022,Posted: 10 February,all,Varathius,"One of the best RTS games of all time (next to homeworld 1/2), followed closely by Ground Control and the original C&C when Westwood studios was still in business.The good:- Beautiful, beautiful graphics!- You indeed feel that you are in the Homeworld universe.- Amazing battle chatter- Fun and amazing skirmish- Great campaign storyThe cons:- Lack of support by devs. (adding maps, etc.)- Near extinct Multiplayer (forget 2 v 2, you are lucky to find 1 v 1 at times).- Campaign although nice, could have been longer (approx. 7-8 hr campaign on Normal difficulty).- Towards the end-game when you massed a huge fleet with many units, expect regular FPS drops (I used gtx1080 strix on ultra).Conclusion:This could hands down have been the best modern day RTS game out there! Too bad the game wasn't appropriately advertised, thus less people managed to join from the beginning on, which in my opinion left the devs no other option to let go of the support and love that this game deserves. The game runs flawlessly (win 10), and it is great fun to play some skirmish from time to time. The campaign on medium setting is challenging and on classic (highest setting) is rather hard, so if you are up for a challenge, you're in good hands with this game.Do I recommend it at the current price?- YES. Simply because this is one of the best RTS games out there that for some reason did not get the attention that it should have."
