,Recommended,281610,33747482,Posted: 23 July,all,Sedghammer,"This is one of the best RTS games to come out in years, for several reasons.-Large scale: You'll be fighting over great distances, but simultaneously each unit.-Strategic zoom: Zoom out to see the entire battlefield. All modern strategy games should have this feature.-Veterancy: Each unit has veterancy which rewards unit preservation.-Line of Sight- Line of sight and height advantage are simulated. Use smoke screens to block line of sight for an attack or to screen your retreat. Take to the high ground with your railguns and pick off the enemy without risk.-Combined arms: Units have very distinct roles. Most are specialists, forcing you to use combined arms to be the most effective.-Micro: Unit types allow for lots of interesting and varied engagements. Intel and support are key to closing out the match.-Artifact System: One way to win a match is to collect artifacts, which forces you to play aggressively. Collecting artifacts gives your carrier (basically a mobile base) a boost to its abilities. If you can manage to take your carrier on the offensive you are at a big advantage.TLDR: This is one of the most interesting and feature full RTS games to come out in years. I'd give it a 9.5/10."
