76561198019780115,Not Recommended,281610,20674414,"Posted: 21 January, 2016",all,K.C.,"I could go on and on about what's awesome and what is just flat out wrong with this game for hours. I might even make a review about it on youtube, since there's a lot to discuss. In the end however, to do that here would end up in a TL:DR for most people. So I will simply say this:  when compared to Command and Conquer (C&C) 3, arguably the greatest land-based RTS game ever created (and from where I think this game got a lot of its inspiration from), this newest title of the beloved Homeworld franchise falls short of the RTS genre standard in its current state. In truth the game, without all of the bugs it has right now (and they are Legion, even causing my game to crash while in a skirmish here and there), comes off a lot more like C&C 4--what with the whole mobile base and hardly any fixed structures thing.Don't get me wrong. I like this game. I think it has massive potential. But the gameplay is restrictive, nothing on the villain's side I've played seems to work, In fact the Gaalsiens seem very rushed. And overall there seems to be an insufficient amount of asymmetrical gameplay between the two factions. It is there, but there could be more, WAY more.That all briefly said, I cannot recommend this game where it is now. Although, I do trust that there will be patches and definite DLC content added to this game. Being a student of business and the entrainment industry, I know what the developers have done with this title. It's a thing that's happening all over film, television, and gaming right now. It's this idea that ""less is more."" And in the case of Homeworld:  Deserts of Kharak, delivering LESS very much equals the fans wanting MORE. Gearbox, Blackbird, I WANT MORE! So they've done their jobs. What I'm asking for NOW is that this game receives the love, through patching, that it deserves. Get it working, place more unit variety in the game with more unique abilities, and it will be great! I just know it.*And for godsakes! Please remove the Gaalsien assualt cruiser as a coalition build option! It's utterly immersion breaking! And get a third faction in there! One with a flying carrier that's heavily reliant on support/assualt aircraft! As I said, MORE!Good job."
