76561198051814897,Recommended,281610,35026173,Posted: 17 September,all,SiNiSTRAE,"When first playing this game I assumed it was going to be a turn-based that reset all troop deployments and resources at the beginning of the mission; not so.  Your decisions carry weight as each loss or misuse of a resource will carry over into the next mission.  This adds a welcomed weight to the genre and begs you to consider your strategy more carefully and not simply throw numbers of troops at the opposition.The flow of the game is also nice as you play it like reading an english book (left to right) so you constantly get the sense that you are actually on this desperate trek across Kharak.  The graphics, sounds, and voice acting are all of good quality as well and it is always nice to see a creative new spin on vehicles such as land carriers.Overall a solid 8/10"
