76561197966537248,Recommended,281610,20672707,"Posted: 21 January, 2016",all,/HDF/Draslin,"So far, game is very entertaining.  Much nostalgia.  Missions are fast and furious, so if you're expecting a slow easy pace like Starcraft 2's campaign, you will be disappointed.  Air units are pretty strong, and mistakes are pretty punishing.The game, like the remastered version of Homeworld 2, does not allow you to manually progress to the next mission.  This results in many lost minerals and artifacts if you progress on the main objectives at a fast pace.  The end result is that you start the next mission without the resources required to get off to a decent start.  This can be VERY frustrating!Only other complaint is that most of the strike units are pretty boring.  Gone are the Ion Frigates, support corvettes, and other smaller units that made their mark on the homeworld franchise.  Instead, it's a bunch of trucks that all sort of seem to do the same thing, or very close to it.  The game is very heavily focused around fighter and corvette equivalent class vessels, and more than halfway through the story, I can't build anything bigger yet.  Makes for some frustrating gameplay, especially considering how flimsy those vehicles are and how impossible that makes maintaining veteran units.I'll update this review when I finish my playthrough, but for right now, I'm giving this a recommend based 90% on the fact that it's Homeworld and 10% on the quality of the game itself."
