,Recommended,281610,20684474,"Posted: 22 January, 2016",all,"Prof. Dr. Sir Lord Master, Esq.","(Some spoilers for those who haven't played Homeworld)If you enjoyed the original Homeworld game, then you'll enjoy this sandy romp through the desert.You've got the familiar structure of units and strategy built around a central mobile base, you've got a heirarchy of units that each have that rock vs paper vs scissors tactical system at the low end, and a moving story about people fighting against the odds in the pursuit of truth + salvation in the face of tyranny.Everything a good Homeworld game needs.My only complaints are that the pacing of the game is forcibly fast, and the ending is a bit too succint in my opinion.(Spoilers for Deserts of Kharak, don't read on unless you don't mind the risk )Don't get me wrong, I enjoy all that is here, I just wish that the game wouldn't force certain conflicts that'll end the map, I can count 3~4 instances where a final battle on a map is forced because the enemy is rushing at me and I pretty much have little choice but to bring the hammer down.  I think this sort of tactic should be reserved for the classic difficulty, or add another mid boss type enemy that'll chase you down, but maybe save a final objective for when the player wishes to end it, for easy and / or normal difficulty anyhoo.Again my complaint is when the final objective that will end a map happens to be a boss type character that is chasing the Kapisi down, forcing an early end of a map, I don't mind if the enemy is throwing other groups of enemies or challenges at the kapisi, I just don't like having the map end so fast because the final objective is chasing the kapisi, this just shortens the game overall, I'm sure I would've gleefully enjoyed a few more hours recovering any and all artifacts and resources on each of the maps, and my overall playtime would've been closer to 15 ~ 20 hrs at least, and I would've been happier for it.The impatient players can always go 