76561198005630513,Recommended,281610,20723502,"Posted: 24 January, 2016",all,Scorch,"This is an excellent and well designed RTS game, which is stays true to the original series in terms of gameplay and overall feeling, despite all action comes down from space to the ground.Pros:- 10-12 hours long singleplayer campaign with various missions and interesting story.- Outsanding art design. Just the sight of your fleet moving through desert at night can give you an aesthetic enjoyment.- Sound effects, music and units voice overs are 10/10.- On highest setting game looks very good and runs smooth on my 2014's hardware.- Quite balanced and fun gameplay in the best traditions of Homeworld series. There are two faction which looks similar to each other at first, but they have different strategies and tactics to dominate the desert battlefield. This reminds me Hiigarans and Vaygr from Homeworld 2, though the Coalition and Gaalsiens have even more differences.Cons:- Just a five maps for skirmish and multiplayer. Developers already promissed more as free updates.- Very few option settings for skirmish and MP- Limping Gaalsien AI in skirmish. The Coalition one is much more aggressive even on easy, but still suffers from lack of ""cunning"" and variety of tactics.- There is no way to change hotkeys for now.Despite its minor and temporal flaws I can recommend this game to anyone who is looking for good singleplayer experience in RTS. Multiplayer is somewhat lacking for now, but I'm sure things will be fixed quite soon and more content will be added."
