,Not Recommended,281610,20675892,"Posted: 22 January, 2016",all,www,"[     ] Buy now[ ✔ ] Wait for patches[ ✔ ] Wait for sale[     ] AvoidGeneral GameplayIn terms of performance and integrity, the game is rock solid. I've yet to encounter any bugs or crashes, a huge contrast from playing Fallout 4's infestation of (mostly non-breaking) bugs. The developers did well doing QA on this game.Response time is excellent and pathing is mostly fantastic. I've yet to witness any issues with units being stuck or causing unwanted collisions. With that said, all the maps are open deserts with minimal obstructions so not much can go wrong.There's only about a dozen units per faction and the other faction has a mirroring unit with minor differences. This is far from being comparable to Starcraft 2 nor Company of Heroes 2. You can dumb it down to being a two dimensional plane version of Homeworld but it's much more refreshing to play.Single Player CampaignOverall, I enjoyed the single player campaign experience but it was lucklustre. I just wish there was more going on, be it in the background or actively part of the campaign. There's no ""critters"" or random environment props and units disappear after being destroyed. To be fair, there were sand storms in one of the missions.I don't consider myself to be an RTS expert and I don't think my APM is high enough to brag about, but I managed to complete the campaign on the hardest difficulty and was only defeated twice - once on two seperate missions.The campaign is also linear and you only get to play as one of the two factions in the game. I was actually hoping that I get to play another 13 missions as the opposing faction. However, the amount of detail and production to produce the cutscenes and dialogue was fantastic!There's no ingame mechanic to compel you to replay the campaign again, once you finish it on hardest mode, you get 3 out of a maximum of 3 stars. It'd be fantastic to see how well you did on different runs of the campaign, particularly stats that show how much resources/time/etc were made during that run. Would also be fun to see how you fare against your friends!Multiplayer / SkirmishThere's only 5 maps. No joke.The only challenge you find here is if you play multiplayer against real players, the AI, for the time being, is way too easy than it should be.There's two modes that you can choose to play, artefact retrieval and annihilation. Artefact retrieval is an interesting idea, artefacts are spawned based off a timer mechanic and the first player/team to meet the target amount wins.There is also a unit cap of 125 in multiplayer, which feels unusual and I suspect there is a reason to this other than fps performance or balance.Considering the abysmal amount of maps included, if they had additional multiplayer modes such as King of the Hill or Company of Heroes' Capture the Flag/Points, that would at least give players more options to play with.The developers have included skins/theme mechanic for players to customise their army colours but I wasn't able to pick a different theme other than the default. You can change the primary and secondary paint scheme though, so that's something I guess.Final ThoughtsWhile I appreciate the amount of work that has been put into this game, particularly the single player campaign, I simply cannot justify the price.I just finished a comp stomp in Company of Heroes 2 and I definately enjoyed that more than the skirmish experience in this game.Wishlist:An additional single player campaign. DLC for the Gaalsian?Additional faction to differentiate between the existing twoNeeds more units and/or secondary active abilities. (Carrier with docking capabilities?)Additional multiplayer modes and winning condition optionsHarder AIReasons to replay the campaignMore multiplayer maps$15-$30 expansionUltimately, I think the game is great and the developers are incredibly talented. At this point of time I cannot recommend this game to others, despite my enjoyment. I am, however, extremely confident that any additional content, be it patch, DLC or expansion by this team will be well polished and content rich!"
