y displayed. There's no real interaction between units and where there is it's done in a very joyless fashion. Harvesters just bob back and forth between resources and resource controller, no docking and unloading, just ""boop"" and it's all unloaded and back to work once it gets close enough. No docking of your land units with your land carrier, only fighters can and they're really more of just an additional carrier special ability. There's none of the nice interactions of units like in Homeworld.Maybe I'm just tired and grouchy, sick of constant crashes. I'll revisit this review as and when there is a patch, though I doubt anything will be done to fix any of my main gripes so far. Don't worry though, I hear some paid DLC will be coming soon, woopdidoo, have some more nostalgia money.Edit: So two patches in and there have been minor balance changes... no bug fixes. Wonderful.And BBI seem to just be letting the Steam forums fester instead of maintaining or posting information in them. I feel this game is just going to fizzle out.Edit 2: I played through bugs and crashes and 13 missions for a 10 second outro? Are you kidding me? This game is worth about £10 at most. Terrible story telling and a waste of the franchise and the good ideas it used up pointlessly."
