76561197993453957,Recommended,281610,20650691,"Posted: 20 January, 2016",all,Pentraksil,"Review will be updated as I go through it.Huge fan of Homeworld franchise and I am having a blast with Deserts of Kharak!Played only the campaign but it is amazing so far. The entire game feels like Homeworld. Amazing sound design, hearing the chatter of the nearby units is a truly immersive experience. Chatter is not active only durring battles, when units are idle there are a lot of talking going on. Amazing stuff.I didn't expect the UI design to be this good, the navigation is simple and no need to juggle between numerous screens. The only negative here is the rebinding. It is not possible to do it, it should be a standard when it comes to PC gaming. But the presets are very well done so not a huge issue for me there. But I agree that there is no excuse for leaving it out.Graphic quality is on par with the entire HW feel, someone might argue that the AA and shadow quality could have been better, but it is unnoticable when you are having a good time with the game. The entire feel, atmosphere, combat sounds, the movement and physics of the vehicles.....simply amazing. The detail on the units is uncanny, with a lot of personal touches, makes all those vehicle look believable and real. The game also runs very well on my system, I was a bit worried since I saw some people have issues with 980TI  ( I have i5 8gb RAM GTX 970). All on ULTRA, no  issues at all, even during huge battles.Gameplay is also top notch. I see a lot of people worried about the number of units and I have to ask you: What happened to quality over quantity? I agree, on paper it looks meager, but when you take the reins of the game it is obvious that each unit has it's purpose. Every unit has it's weakness and it's strength and they support each other marvelously. The feeling of sending your LAV's to charge the long range artilery, while your tanks provide smoke cover is simply amazing. You activate the boosts for LAV's while they fly over the dunes while firework spectacle around them begins to unravel....Air support kicks in just in time to help the assault.....You harass the enemy and start ""boosting"" your retreat to the nearest Support vehicle for repairs, dust coulds all around you.....Another succesfull attack....Simply AMAZING! More units =/= more tactical option. It is much more important (for me at least) to have units that have it's purpose. The situation reminds me of Shogun 2 and the backlash that it caused with the info that unit number will be small (compared to other TW) and factions will be very similar. It turned out great for TW, much better then adding a bunch of very similar units with no real purpose on the battlefield. As I said: Quality over Quantity.Now for some negatives:No formations...This hurts me the most it seems, the game really needs it. Ordering units to move or to attack is a nightmare if it is a mixed group, each unit moves at their own max speed. It is a tactical disaster, it can be bypased by micromanaging each unit group separately but it can be a pain.The game has some cliping issues. It is an RTS but it really looks ugly sometimes when Kapisi just rolls over S'jet, without S'jet moving an inch. There is also an issue when you group some units together. It can look ugly and it can ruin the immersion. But sometimes, when the collision works like it should, units can get stuck. My resource collectors got stuck in a loop and I didn't even notice, the lack of resources almost costed me a battle. It is not often but it can happen.AI has it's flaws. I haven't tried skirmish yet, but I have seen a lot of proof that it is not the best. I haven't noticed it too much during campaign, it was actually suprisingly good there (they are retreating heavy artillery and tanks if they don't have light unit support etc.) but you can see some signs of ""stupidity"" (rushing positions etc.)The above mentioned rebinding issue.Only 5 skirmish maps. This is a rather small number, HW never had an abundance of maps, but land RTS should have some more variety.All in all I am having a blast. Fun game, great campaign, just as I expected. Some might argue that the price is a bit high. For now, I am having my moneys worth, people are also forgetting that you could get 3 amazing games for that price or an discount as an owner of Remastered.  For the fun I am having, it is a fair price. Could have been better when it comes to MP content, but I am sure that we will have a lot of content down the road (BBI confirmed new maps, all for free with additional DLC/Expansion plans)Great game :)"
