76561197963326166,Not Recommended,281610,20697459,"Posted: 23 January, 2016",all,Tigrid,"So disappointed, was really looking forward to this.This game was not ready for release and does not live up to its heritage.Have requested a refund.As other reviewers have said, and in no particular order:- shoddy animations- shoddy physics- selecting units can sometimes be difficult and behaves inconsistently- inconsistent texturing (though some of it is beautiful)- a carrier that doesn't carry anything- resource harvesters that don't actually visibly return resources, just pull up 100m away from the carrier, pause and then continue.- pathing management with large vehicles and somewhat enclosed spaces is clumsy- backstory isn't particularly well presented, more implicit than anything else- semi-adoption of Homeworld keyboard shortcuts, but pressing 'f' to focus doesn't really work, double tapping it does nothing- no alt-select for focus- camera controls don't seem intuitive- camera can not be zoomed out far enough, forced into the sensor view 90% of the time, even though the maps aren't that large- only a handful of skirmish maps- AI is lacking in the campaignThe biggest problem though is one of the games core mechanics, the effect that elevation has on combat:- an overlay is displayed with elevation hints when you are issuing move or attack-move commands but this info is unavailable if you're simply right clicking to issue move commands. A keyboard key to toggle the overlay would have been more useful.- positioning units, particularly large groups of units, to take advantage of elevation is virtually impossible as there are:- no formations for units- no way of specifying the orientation of units or groups of units- despite LOS being such an important mechanic, you will often find half your units have none, and there's little you can do about it.I love the concept and art design. The UI is fine. Music is spot on and the Story is OK, just under presented.I think most punters were surprised when this was announced. Almost seems like the release date was a little bit of a surprise for the developers - seems as if they were rushed into getting this out the door well before it was ready, otherwise I would be DEEPLY surprised if all these game dev vets who were supposedly working on the title would have been content shipping it.If development continues post release and some of the above gets fixed, I would gladly change my review. Would love to this title shine."
