,Not Recommended,281610,29441412,Posted: 23 January,all,LeMador [TH],"i bought this game for the nostalgia factor after i played the original Homeworld and Homeworld2 in early 2000s.. since then, there has been a number of better RTS games than Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak.. games such as Starcraft2 and the Red Alert series, that i would recommend over Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak ..without the nostalgia factor, i guess i would be more disappointed and more critical with Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak..the graphics is great and the zoom close-up during battles, is definitely impressive.. but the story is very very minimalistic following the style of the previous 2 games.. however, the previous 2 games came-out in a time when PC gaming was in its early infancy.. maybe early childhood..the technology of the time did not allow Homeworld and Homeworld2 to have complicated game-play and top-notch cinematics.. so the style of the game had to be as minimal as possible to work in most computers in early 2000..but Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak, came in a time when there is so much more that could have been done to the game..   just look at Starcraft2..i dunno.. Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak just feels ""lazy"" to me, compared to what Starcraft and Command and Conquer had become.. and compared to the original Homeworld and Homeworld2..FURTHERMORE.. and this is a BIG one!.. the reason why i loved Homeworld and Homeworld2 so much, is because the battles took place in outer-space, where you had to navigate in a 3D space and you had to move your units along with x, y and z axis..at the time (in early 2000) Homeworld and Homeworld2 were the best space RTS game in a truly 3D enviroment..no other game came close to what the original developers of Homeworld and Homeworld2 have achieved..Homeworld: Deserts of Kharak, did not add anything new that felt groundbreaking..so ok.. I AM A SCI-FI JUNKY.. AND I WANT TO SEE MORE SPACE BATTLES!!and i find my fix with Starwars, StarTrek, StarGate, Ba