,Recommended,281610,20755867,"Posted: 25 January, 2016",all,Eagle,"Still chugging along, but I feel I've played enough that my feelings are set.  This game is just 'eh'.It does everything right, but nothing stands out.  I like that units carry over, but resources are so plentiful (classic mode) that losing half your fleet is recoverable.  Units are well balanced, and there's enough variety to their abilities that a diversified force is useful.But it's just so boring.  Cut scenes don't leave an impression, but you can't skip them.  The campaign matches will end at near random points, and your ai isn't smart enough to grab the extra resources before moving on to the next zone.  The enemy ai is pathetic.  The long range rail guns will role within range of all other vehicles, so rushing them with LAVs, while useful, isn't necessary.  The maps all start to look the same.  Yes, I get this is in a desert, but give us something to look at.  The music fits the theme, but is so slow that it will lull you to sleep while your main base holds off ten armored vehicles and your scavengers run around unharassed.So yes, it does everything right, but somehow gets it wrong.  I play one match, then get too bored to continue and put off the next level for a day.  That's something I never did with C&C or StarCraft.  Even planetary annihilation, massive flop that it was, would entertain me for 4-5 hours before I tucked it away again.TL:DR.  I recommend this game as it has an interesting mechanics combination, but only if it's on sale."
