76561198079225453,Recommended,281610,27718998,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,Fedaykin,"Much better than I expected.Pros:- Good writing and very immersive campaign- Challenging in a good way (forces you to actually think to succeed)- Got a lot of the details right (i.e. using high ground for artillery, forcing you to be careful about deploying aircraft)- Very fun gameplay overall.  Some missions in the campaign have a very high replayability factor.- It has a neat nostalgia factor if you played the orginal Homeworld games.  Lots of parallels there, but this game is very different and stands on its own.Cons:- Inability to issue commands while paused.  For me that's not a big issue, but for some it may create anxiety because you are forced to react at the game's speed.  You do not have the ability to pause, look around, and create strategy.  Everything is on the fly.- Lack of multiplayer options.  Only a couple of gameplay modes and several of the ""usual"" configurable options are missing, such as: starting resources, game speed, starting research, etc.- Multiplayer lacking some depth.  There are very hard counters to each tech tree.  You have light armor?  I'll make heavy armor.  You have heavy armor?  I'll make artillery.  You have artillery?  I'll make light armor.  Throw in some (admittedly very good) air power and that's about as deep as it goes.Overall:Worth the buy for the campaign.  I will probably replay several of the campaign scenarios and may explore the DLC.  I may play a multiplayer A.I. skirmish on rare occasion.  I expect I'll end up with around 50 hours played time on it, which is respectable."
