,Not Recommended,281610,28319619,"Posted: 11 December, 2016",all,S. Gordon,"Well... were shall I start.Is DOK (aka Homeworld Shipbreakers) a game you should get ? Graphic wise it's a masterpiece, gameplay wise it sucks balls and it is a frustrating experience.The pros:- Graphic wise, (apart from a few glitches which I will turn a blind eye on here) the game is absolutely beautiful.- The story as far as I am now is ok by Homeworld standardsThe cons:- No tutorial to speak off. It takes trial and error as to know what units are great against others; see next in line:- Capturing enemy missile ships (who are strong against strike craft) seemed like a good idea ? They won't lift a finger against sandskimmers and just sit there while they are cut to ribbons.- The pathfinding of some units (especially Rachel's Runner) can sometimes be very clunky. It can mean a lot of frustration when she is under fire, which happens a lot!- Why not call a cat a cat and call the 'Runner' a 'Crawler' since it's slow as molasses.-Why oh why did we not get a 'stance button', this is an RTS after all,  which could come in handy if you are waiting for your capture ability to cool down without risking to destroy it since firing at a unit seems to be standard modus operandi of all units.- WTF have the devs done with the Tactical Pause option which was a trademark of the Homeworld games ?- Rachel sometimes ignores given orders, one needs to click the capture icon again to have effect.- Player units who need to stay put (like the railguns) just pursue their targets. They are defensive units, they should act defensively. (again, the stance button would be a valid addition to the game here!)- What good is a Carrier that cannot repair or dock units ?- The escape button does not bring up the menu, very original but everything but intuitive!- Rachel's 'Crawler' under 25% health should have the self preservation to run by herself since she is a critical unit. I should not have to micromanage this behaviour, again, a stance button could help a lot here.So my final account at this moment is:I 'm glad I bought it on sale at 50 % off. I would have kicked myself for buying this at full price. Solving the issues above would do a great deal in making this mediocre game a lot better. But until that happens... meh!"
