76561198006689642,Recommended,281610,33917026,Posted: 30 July,all,Ferex,"Nice game which tells the pre story of the original homeworld title.It's very nice to see, that the developers tried to keep the game mechanics of the original game.Even though I personally liked the real 3d-space-battles better I found it nice to have the chance to get an insight into the pre story of the original homeworld.In short: I recommend this title to all the fans of the original game, even though the game play itself can't reach the level of the real and unfortunatelly only homeworld title"
76561197988111894,Recommended,281610,34021039,Posted: 4 August,all,Mister Chalk,"This is a very well polished game, and I love the deep and interesting backstory presented about the fascanating culture and history of Kharak. The gameplay is fairly solid and certainly fast-paced, thrumming with that middle-eastern ""Dune"" desert sci-fi that I can't get enough of. For those points, it's a solid thumbs-up. Read up on the delicious backstory and you'll love every moment of the campaign.On the other hand, you do sometimes end up playing against the game rather than the enemy - I find the control groups are awkward to assign and clear in the heat of the particularly fast battles. Similarly, whilst I can unhappily absorb the lack of formations, it can be hard to ascertain the minutae of what exactly is going on and where: a Total War style pause button wouldn't have gone amiss for moving large intricate formations or responding to multiple distant threats. The enemy AI is reasonably good but ""cheats"" by not playing to the same rules as the player, at least in terms of economy and resource gathering, which makes conditions feel a little unfair in a protracted battle.So it's got some cons, but it's a great story and interesting world to inhabit. Just make sure to read up using the backstory app and, apart from suffering through some occasionally poor gameplay design, you'll have a great time."
